 "draftNote": "1 of five queued off a bottom-two lane: Mr_Meat31 (midlane→offlane).",
 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A clean objective win — 87k-19k on objectives and 26-15 in neutrals, even with the carry lane on the back foot.",
  "team": "You won the map, not the lanes. Objective damage was 87k to 19k and you took neutrals 26-15, despite Cuban's Sparrow being down in lane to Murdock (theirs all game, first tower lost). Mr_Meat31's The Fey (5/3/10, team-high 27.8k) and Goldilocks' Iggy (7/4/8, 28k) were the engines, Xeebs' Khaimera anchored 34k objective damage, and Willy's Steel chipped in 12 assists. Keep snowballing objectives off your mid/offlane tempo.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Objective tempo beat lane parity — you turned a losing carry lane into a win by grouping for objectives (87k-19k). Same plan next time.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "The Fey mid, 5/3/10 and team-high 27.8k — yours at every checkpoint vs Legion, with your Wraith Leggings spike landing ~19m. Your career stat rates offlane as your best role, but The Fey mid keeps over-delivering; worth treating as a real main, and that early lane lead is exactly the tempo to start the Fangtooth/Prime calls off.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Iggy offlane, 7/4/8 with 28k damage and 25k into objectives — even early then yours from 15 minutes on vs Zarus, and you used that window to wreck objectives. Exactly the tempo offlaner this comp wanted. Clean game.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera jungle, 8/6/5 and team-high 34k objective damage — yours at every checkpoint vs Boris, and you anchored the macro lead. Build note: you skipped armor (Overlord/Basilisk) into a 4-physical enemy comp; pick it up when you see that draft.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Sparrow into Murdock was an uphill lane (theirs from the second checkpoint on, first tower lost) and 4/3/3 is a fine hold — but your core was off-meta (no Storm Breaker/Sky Splitter/Spectra) so your spikes came late (Vanquisher ~25m, Imperator ~36m). The standard core spikes harder and would've turned the lane sooner.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Steel support, 2/4/12 — your lane was even early then yours from 15 minutes on vs Narbash, and 12 assists is real enabling. Still, Steel isn't your edge: your Belica (56%) and Zinx (56%) give the team more than a 15.7k tank support."
  }
 },
